23/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov publicly revealed on Monday (22 May) his and his family's holdings, in a declaration submitted to the Chief Auditor's Office. A copy of the document was also published on the president's Web site. Parvanov urged all senior politicians and state officials to follow his example, stressing that there must be maximum transparency regarding the incomes of public figures, to strengthen the fight against corruption.
In other news, delegations from Bulgaria and Macedonia are visiting the Vatican to mark the Day of Saint Cyril and Methodius, the fathers of the Slavonic alphabet. The Macedonian delegation, headed by President Branko Crvenkovski, met with Pope Benedict XVI on Monday. On Tuesday, the pontiff was scheduled to meet with the Bulgarian delegation, led by Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev. (Monitor, Darik - 23/05/06; BNR - 22/05/06)
